Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper analyzes the evolution of incoming and outgoing links from and to media pages, which can be considered as a social network. 
2. cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) - Similar to the above, the paper studies the Media Web, which is a subset of the larger social network of the Web. 
3. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper discusses the appearance of new media content on the Web, which is related to information retrieval. 
4. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) - The paper analyzes the Media Web, which can be considered as a digital library of media content. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper focuses on media content on the Web, which falls under the scope of multimedia research.
